      • i_see_x_rows_in_a_table

        @Then(value="^I see (\\d+) rows in the (.*)$")
public static void i_see_x_rows_in_a_table(int expectedNumberOfRows,
                                                                                          String elementName)
                                                                                   throws Throwable
        Verifies we have the expected, given number of rows in the given string representing the Table object. The string is made lower case and whitespaces are replaced with underscores, then it is sent a getNumberOfRows event and returns the number of rows in the table. The page object and driver object are defined by the WebDriverFactory and PageFactory objects. The derived Page Object (extends Page) should define a method named [element name]_[element type] returning a Table object (e.g. results_table).

        NOTE: Headers defined with a <th> tag will not be counted. If a row has a <tr> tag and a class of "header", it will be counted.

        Gherkin Examples:

        • I see 10 rows in the results table
        • I see 20 rows in the User List Table
        • I see 5 rows in the Current Year Documents table
        Parameters:
        expectedNumberOfRows - int The number of rows your are expecting.
        elementName - String (Table name) This should be the name of the table element to count.
        Throws:
        Throwable - this exists so that any uncaught exceptions result in the test failing

      • i_verify_an_element_exists

        @Then(value="^I verify (?:the|a|an) (.*?)( does not)?(?: does)? exists?$")
public static void i_verify_an_element_exists(String elementName,
                                                                                                                         String assertion)
                                                                                                                  throws Throwable
        Verifies the given element exists. The given element string is made lower case and whitespaces are replaced with underscores, then it is sent the isDisplayed event and returns true or false. It also has an assertion variable which is set if the words "does not" are used, and it looks for a negative assertion. The word "does" can be used optionally, and was added to support the use of a Scenario Outline which switches between "does" and "does not" in its tests.

        Gherkin Examples:

        • I verify a submit button exists
        • I verify the Plan Dropdown does not exist
        • I verify an area map does exist
        Scenario Outline Example:

        I verify the <element> <Assertion> exist

        Examples: <table summary="Examples"> <tr> <td>| element</td> <td>| Assertion</td> <td>|</td> </tr> <tr> <td>| first dropdown</td> <td>| does</td> <td>|</td> </tr> <tr> <td>| second dropdown</td> <td>| does not</td> <td>|</td> </tr> </table>

        Parameters:
        elementName - String Element to check
        assertion - String "does" or does not" for true or false
        Throws:
        Throwable - this exists so that any uncaught exceptions result in the test failing

      • i_see_the_text_appears_on_pages_of_the_pdf

        @Then(value="^I see the text (.*) appears (?:on|between) the (\\d+)(?:st|nd|rd|th)(?: and )?(\\d+)?(?:st|nd|rd|th)? pages? of the pdf$")
public void i_see_the_text_appears_on_pages_of_the_pdf(String text_to_verify,
                                                                                                                                                                                                int firstPageNumber,
                                                                                                                                                                                                Integer lastPageNumber)
                                                                                                                                                                                         throws Throwable
        Validates whether the currently open pdf contains the given text on the page(s) passed to it. If a page number is passed for the first page and a null is passed for the second page, then only that page is searched. If two page numbers are passed, then the entire range is searched, inclusive of the two page numbers given.

        Gherkin Examples:

        • Then I see the text Validation Text appears on the 3rd page of the pdf
        • Then I see the text 1Q2W3E_4R5T appears between the 1st and 4th pages of the pdf
        NOTE: This will fail if the browser window is not currently open with a pdf loaded. Should be executed after the i_open_the_document_with_extension_in_a_new_tab(linkName,extension) method is called. The cucumber step is: @When("^I open the (.*) (pdf) in a new tab$")

        Parameters:
        text_to_verify - String the text string expected to appear in the currently open PDF file
        firstPageNumber - int the page to check or the first page in the range if the second value is not null
        lastPageNumber - Integer the last page in the range; indicates to only check one page if set to null
        Throws:
        Throwable - if any errors are raised they will fail the current test

      • i_verify_the_element_contains_the_text

        @Then(value="^I verify the (.*?)( does not)? (has|have|contains?) the text \"([^\"]*)\"$")
public void i_verify_the_element_contains_the_text(String elementName,
                                                                                                                                              String assertion,
                                                                                                                                              String matchType,
                                                                                                                                              String text)
                                                                                                                                       throws Throwable
        Used to verify that an element contains certain text. It takes an element name and then an optional "does not", which if present means that the method will look for the text to not exist. Then it will look for the words has|have to do an exact match or contain(s) to do a partial match. It uses the text contained in double quotes for matching.

        NOTE: If "URL" (without the quotes) is passed in all caps in place of the element name, This step will check for the text to exist in the current page URL.

        Gherkin Examples:

        • I verify the header div contains the text "Header"
        • I verify the state dropdown does not contain the text "VA"
        • I verify the paragraph div has the text "This is my example text."
        • I verify the street name textbox does not have the text "P.O. Box"
        • I verify the url http://google.com has the text "google"
        Parameters:
        elementName - String The name of the element to be evaluated as defined in the page object.
        assertion - String Evaluated as a boolean, where null = false and any text = true.
        matchType - String whether we are doing an exact match or a partial match
        text - String The text to verify exists in the element.
        Throws:
        Throwable - Throws any errors passed to it.

      • i_verify_the_selection_contains_the_text

        @Then(value="^I verify the (.*?)( does not)? (?:has|have) the text \"([^\"]*)\" selected$")
public void i_verify_the_selection_contains_the_text(String elementName,
                                                                                                                                                 String assertion,
                                                                                                                                                 String text)
                                                                                                                                          throws Throwable
        Used to verify that the selected option of a select element contains certain text. It takes an element name and then an optional "does not", which if present means that the method will look for the text to not exist. Then it will look for any of the words has|have and uses the text contained in double quotes for matching.

        Gherkin Examples:

        • I verify the Area Select Box has the text "This is my example text." selected
        • I verify the cola radio button does not have the text "Root beer" selected
        Parameters:
        elementName - String Name of the Element to verify
        assertion - String if empty we expect this to be false
        text - String Text to match
        Throws:
        Throwable - this exists so that any uncaught exceptions result in the test failing
